{
  "texts": [
    "It facilitates human-like audio analysis by converting the linear frequency scale into a perceptually appropriate mel-frequency scale 34.",
    "To determine the value of each element, a computation is performed by taking the average of all the numbers obtained within each frame, followed by the subtraction of their respective standard deviations.",
    "A spectrum energy map was generated for the Mel scale by applying the Fourier transform (using the window abbreviation) to the signal.",
    "This was done using the MFCC series of infant audio recordings.",
    "Subsequently, by employing an independent cosine transformation on the Mel log energy array, extract the logarithms of the power values."
  ]
}